21
00:01:26,214 --> 00:01:28,350
When'd you get back?

22
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:30,423
Two weeks ago?

23
00:01:30,796 --> 00:01:32,143
And how's the family?

24
00:01:32,143 --> 00:01:35,768
Out of my life... I got divorced...

25
00:01:35,768 --> 00:01:39,230
Really? But Shilpa was so nice!

26
00:01:39,230 --> 00:01:43,740
Aye, the women are always nice... We're the nasty ones...

27
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:47,474
Stop it, Raj... You haven't changed one bit from your college days, have you?

28
00:01:47,474 --> 00:01:50,494
Do you remember those days?

29
00:01:55,260 --> 00:01:57,330
Can't forget them...

30
00:01:57,950 --> 00:02:02,270
I've made it through all these years thanks to the memories...

31
00:02:02,270 --> 00:02:05,920
You know about Vijay...

32
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:09,050
He's always been deployed in conflict zones...

33
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:15,626
And I used to tease you for it... Vijay's been cruel to me... Claimed you for himself...

34
00:02:16,263 --> 00:02:18,261
But honestly...

35
00:02:18,261 --> 00:02:22,601
I really feel sad for you... You made a great couple...

36
00:02:22,890 --> 00:02:24,297
Aye...

37
00:02:25,110 --> 00:02:27,620
He was my world...

38
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:30,715
I miss him every living moment...

39
00:02:30,715 --> 00:02:32,530
I can understand...

40
00:02:32,530 --> 00:02:36,223
How's Vishal?
-Great. He's doing his A-Levels...

41
00:02:36,223 --> 00:02:41,460
Last year of school... About time he started planning things...

42
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:45,294
Really? I thought he'd be sitting his GCSEs this year...

43
00:02:45,294 --> 00:02:48,919
And your daughters?
-They're just eight...

44
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:51,830
And your son -- What's his name?
-Vipin.

45
00:02:51,830 --> 00:02:54,570
Aye, right... How's he?

46
00:02:54,570 --> 00:03:00,390
He's with Shilpa... I talk to him now and then... Not her though...

47
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:02,592
Bitter divorce...

48
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:04,618
Bitter divorce?

49
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:10,890
She had an affair, and it wasn't easy for me, but I asked for it myself...

50
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:13,548
She's remarried now...

51
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,453
Hmm...

52
00:03:16,715 --> 00:03:21,109
Aye... I'm sure it hurts...

53
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:24,339
She hit me where it hurts...

54
00:03:24,339 --> 00:03:30,800
Vipin left for University... And I got transferred back to India...

55
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,500
I can't stay anywhere long.

56
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:36,610
Just trying to reconnect with old friends since I got here...

57
00:03:36,610 --> 00:03:40,981
Just trying to cope with my depression, you could say...

58
00:03:42,366 --> 00:03:48,280
It was a heartbreak... But not as big as when Vijay made you his.

59
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:50,675
Please, Raj...

60
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,592
Sunanda...

61
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:59,774
What if I proposed to you again?

62
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:21,481
You're the only one who can help...

63
00:04:21,559 --> 00:04:25,229
I wouldn't have had to ask you if Sherali were here...

64
00:04:25,288 --> 00:04:28,396
You know how much he loved me...

65
00:04:28,459 --> 00:04:34,910
I need some time to think... But don't worry... I'll do something...

66
00:04:35,749 --> 00:04:40,052
You're the only one I've got now, Amna...

67
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:46,172
Anyway... I'll get back to you, okay?

68
00:04:46,530 --> 00:04:47,597
Okay.

69
00:04:47,597 --> 00:04:51,326
Give my regards to Mum and Dad... Tell the kids I said hi.

70
00:04:51,326 --> 00:04:52,723
Okay.

71
00:04:52,854 --> 00:04:55,020
Okay, bye.

72
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,811
Bye.

73
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:00,820
Who was it?

74
00:05:02,310 --> 00:05:04,448
Aunt Ayesha...

75
00:05:04,448 --> 00:05:07,381
What is it this time?

76
00:05:10,342 --> 00:05:13,500
Zafar's suffered a big loss...

77
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:17,691
She was asking if we could lend her... 6 or 7 million-ish...

78
00:05:18,010 --> 00:05:20,757
6 or 7 <i>million</i>-ish?

79
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:25,540
But how? And why is she asking you?

80
00:05:26,020 --> 00:05:33,453
She's found out about the compensation for your Dad's death...

81
00:05:33,453 --> 00:05:36,189
I hope you turned her down.

82
00:05:36,457 --> 00:05:39,530
I said... I need some time...

83
00:05:39,530 --> 00:05:41,948
You -- Need time?

84
00:05:41,948 --> 00:05:46,857
Remember everything she said when she left! But now, she has the guts to ask for our 'help'!

85
00:05:46,857 --> 00:05:53,508
I've lost count how many times Dad's lent Uncle something... Has he ever returned a penny?

86
00:05:54,330 --> 00:05:58,655
I know... But I can't just turn her down like that...

87
00:05:58,655 --> 00:06:03,424
You know how much your Dad loved her.
-He did...

88
00:06:03,424 --> 00:06:06,452
But did she love us?

89
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:10,496
If she did, she'd know we've got no source of income...

90
00:06:10,496 --> 00:06:15,858
She'd know we can't give away everything we've got left like that.

91
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:21,483
I know, but I can't say it to her face...

92
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:25,223
I said I'll talk to your Grandpa.

93
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:31,199
He'd be happy to help his dearest daughters...

94
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:36,861
Who doesn't love his daughters?

95
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:20,920
Neha is Anurag's niece. She wanted to visit India, so I thought I'd bring her along. Yeah?

96
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,748
Yeah.

97
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:37,893
Let's turn up the music, shall we? Unless... You don't like it?

98
00:07:37,893 --> 00:07:39,722
Sure...

99
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:49,151
♪ <i>That beauty is none but my sweetheart!</i> ♪

100
00:07:54,990 --> 00:07:58,786
Blimey, that's some horrible traffic!

101
00:07:58,786 --> 00:08:01,257
Aye, it ain't nothing like Canada!

102
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:19,947
Whoa! Are you okay? You sure you don't want that seat belt?

103
00:08:19,947 --> 00:08:23,841
Aye, sorry, I just forgot...

104
00:08:24,230 --> 00:08:29,264
Get used to forgetting in this part of the world...
-Okay...

105
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:46,471
Zafar called me too...

106
00:08:47,925 --> 00:08:51,320
Not sure if he told Ayesha, but...

107
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:56,850
He told me if he didn't get the money...

108
00:08:56,850 --> 00:08:59,929
He'd lose his property...

109
00:09:00,613 --> 00:09:03,870
I tried to explain it to him...

110
00:09:05,671 --> 00:09:10,270
But he thinks I've struck gold or something.

111
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:15,687
So... What do we do?

112
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:19,800
We've got the compensation...

113
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:23,229
But we've got duties...

114
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:30,558
He's been asking for a few months... I'm sure he'll pay us back...

115
00:09:30,558 --> 00:09:34,207
What if he didn't?

116
00:09:34,473 --> 00:09:37,337
We can't ask for it...

117
00:09:38,810 --> 00:09:43,567
They've borrowed from Sherali before...

118
00:09:45,064 --> 00:09:47,720
Yeah, from their brother...

119
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:53,980
But they've got to return it to his wife.

120
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:01,483
They know what's going on in your life...

121
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:08,305
Okay... As you say...

122
00:10:08,305 --> 00:10:13,840
I'd never have said it if it were not my own daughter...

123
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:18,061
You know her in-laws very well...

124
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:43,756
And, thanks to your daughter and son-in-law... I can't even look my daughter-in-law in the eye.

125
00:11:17,190 --> 00:11:18,976
Parbhu...

126
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:27,937
How long are you staying here?

127
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:32,862
Can't believe you're asking that the day I'm here.

128
00:11:32,925 --> 00:11:34,835
Naw...

129
00:11:35,521 --> 00:11:37,950
Just... Thinking...

130
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:42,146
I mean...

131
00:11:42,146 --> 00:11:49,395
I'm sure you've -- Got other things to take care of, yes?

132
00:11:49,395 --> 00:11:51,806
Get it?

133
00:11:52,850 --> 00:12:01,337
Granny... I'm here because I wanted to see every place in India I can, and Aunt told me Vishal's gonna show me!

134
00:12:04,710 --> 00:12:06,323
Vishal?

135
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:11,968
Aye. Once he's done with his exams, why not?

136
00:12:11,968 --> 00:12:14,450
I've made a list.

137
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:21,140
Shopping, tourist attractions, and then there's this concert...

138
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:23,880
So many things to do!

139
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:30,731
Neha's a lovely girl... Very friendly and fun-loving. She's just started college, by the way.

140
00:12:30,820 --> 00:12:33,111
Wow. What are you studying?

141
00:12:33,111 --> 00:12:36,936
Art and theatre, but I've got a thing for music too.

142
00:12:36,936 --> 00:12:41,503
Vishal's got a thing for music too. He's quite the singer himself!
-Aye.

143
00:12:41,503 --> 00:12:45,964
So you told me... You've told me a lot about him...

144
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:54,113
Gotta say, this is delicious!
-Have some more!

145
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:05,751
Mum?

146
00:13:05,922 --> 00:13:07,063
Hmm?

147
00:13:07,158 --> 00:13:11,240
You've got to... Talk to Sarah's Mum, remember?

148
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:14,577
Not now, Vishal... Not in front of Pratibha!

149
00:13:14,577 --> 00:13:18,590
Everyone's gonna find out... Say things about you and me...

150
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:20,984
But you've got to say sorry to them.

151
00:13:20,984 --> 00:13:23,936
I will!
-Just do it!

152
00:13:24,138 --> 00:13:30,325
Actually -- It's a bit embarrassing for me too...
-Don't you care too much for --

153
00:13:31,466 --> 00:13:35,537
I just needed a drink.
-It's in the fridge...

154
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:45,066
Nah, not this one...

155
00:13:45,210 --> 00:13:46,923
But...

156
00:13:46,923 --> 00:13:49,053
I guess this will do!

157
00:13:59,590 --> 00:14:05,004
You've mixed your coursebooks with Dad's books...

158
00:14:05,004 --> 00:14:09,710
We shouldn't be lending anything to Aunt. You're making a big mistake.

159
00:14:09,710 --> 00:14:13,480
Back to work, Sarah... Don't get on my wick...

160
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:18,734
I'm not a kid anymore... I can tell you what I think...

161
00:14:19,017 --> 00:14:21,983
Vishal says you're making a mistake too.

162
00:14:21,983 --> 00:14:25,530
Why d'you need to tell him about everything?

163
00:14:25,530 --> 00:14:29,105
Do you need to tell him about everything in our lives?

164
00:14:29,105 --> 00:14:34,626
It's our problem, aye... But you're making a big mistake...

165
00:14:34,650 --> 00:14:38,848
Mark my words, they're not gonna return a penny!

166
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:45,340
I can't turn your Granny and Grandpa down like that.
-They're just thinking of their daughters.

167
00:14:45,340 --> 00:14:51,390
Why do they want our money? D'you think they'd give us a penny if we needed anything?

168
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:03,790
Sarah's right...

169
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:08,504
We don't need to give Ayesha and Zafar a penny...

170
00:15:08,895 --> 00:15:11,690
It's all for Sherali's family...

171
00:15:11,690 --> 00:15:14,406
His kids...

172
00:15:17,090 --> 00:15:18,235
Mum...

173
00:15:18,235 --> 00:15:21,498
Mum! Wait!

174
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:37,178
Shut up the kids, and stop listening to a mature voice of reason! What's next?

175
00:15:44,570 --> 00:15:47,255
Where were you all day?

176
00:15:47,450 --> 00:15:49,879
Too busy...

177
00:15:50,068 --> 00:15:51,910
Honestly knackered...

178
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:54,814
What happened? Your Aunt back?

179
00:15:54,814 --> 00:15:58,277
Aye... How d'you know?

180
00:15:58,277 --> 00:16:00,630
I just do...

181
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:02,695
There's your Aunt...

182
00:16:02,695 --> 00:16:04,933
And then there's mine...

183
00:16:04,933 --> 00:16:12,730
Always something going on... Wonder why we don't empower our women so they don't get blackmailed by their in-laws into blackmailing their families.

184
00:16:12,730 --> 00:16:15,560
Girls are natural blackmailers...

185
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:23,012
Could you not typecast or be so chauvinistic for a change? Like, haven't you got your Granny, your Mum or your sisters?

186
00:16:23,012 --> 00:16:31,060
Thank you for including Granny there... 'Mum and sisters' sounds so stereotypical... Like they all say?

187
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:35,250
I'm anything but stereotypical... Not me, not my life...

188
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,210
What's up with your Aunt?

189
00:16:37,210 --> 00:16:39,845
Oh, nothing... The same old...

190
00:16:39,845 --> 00:16:48,871
She's blackmailing Mum... Grandpa and Granny haven't had anything all day... And I'm the black sheep here! No one wants to talk to me!

191
00:16:50,302 --> 00:16:51,718
Look...

192
00:16:52,201 --> 00:16:57,058
Whatever happens, don't give them a penny. Make it clear to your Mum, okay?

193
00:16:57,058 --> 00:16:59,087
I don't know...

194
00:16:59,493 --> 00:17:05,400
But I think Mum's gonna give up... She won't take up arms against them...

195
00:17:05,470 --> 00:17:09,050
Ain't she a soldier's wife?
-She is...

196
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:13,244
Wives ain't nearly as used to fighting... Even soldiers' wives...

197
00:17:13,244 --> 00:17:16,000
They're only taught to compromise...

198
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,281
What about you?

199
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:20,299
Never.

200
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:22,900
I want to be strong.

201
00:17:22,900 --> 00:17:27,925
Not helpless, cowardly, and dependent.

202
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:31,173
You're outta luck, mate... In Pakistan, at least.

203
00:17:31,173 --> 00:17:36,890
As if it's any different in India. Don't act like you folks don't want doormats for wives.

204
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:39,167
Hardly different.

205
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:46,497
There, now... Don't embarrass me like that...

206
00:17:51,850 --> 00:17:56,270
Your Mum didn't call Mum...

207
00:17:56,490 --> 00:18:01,813
She will... She's got her number... Tell her to take her call, okay?

208
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:09,863
She's talked to a colleague... May be able to help find someone in Pakistan...

209
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:12,328
Anyway...

210
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:16,814
I'm positively knackered... Need some rest.

211
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:20,687
Okay... Good night...

212
00:18:20,687 --> 00:18:24,106
Can't believe you said good night in a second.

213
00:18:25,190 --> 00:18:26,822
You amaze me...

214
00:18:26,822 --> 00:18:27,956
How?

215
00:18:27,956 --> 00:18:32,766
You said you needed some rest. So I said good night. What's wrong?

216
00:18:32,766 --> 00:18:35,076
Nothing, really...

217
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,420
Good night.

218
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:42,736
Good night.

219
00:18:50,850 --> 00:18:52,090
Hello?

220
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:54,464
Hung up...

221
00:19:29,930 --> 00:19:31,564
Mum!

222
00:19:31,735 --> 00:19:33,944
Where's everyone?

223
00:19:45,690 --> 00:19:48,470
Grandpa? Granny? Mum?

224
00:19:48,532 --> 00:19:49,984
Sarah!

225
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,840
What happened?
-Mum!

226
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:56,640
What happened?

227
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:59,249
Elena called! Just got my result!

228
00:19:59,249 --> 00:20:02,010
Yeah?
-Straight A*s!

229
00:20:02,010 --> 00:20:06,426
Best in the school!
-Congratulations!

230
00:20:06,426 --> 00:20:09,856
Did you tell Granny and Grandpa?
-Nope. Wanted to tell you first.

231
00:20:09,856 --> 00:20:13,030
Well done, Sarah.

232
00:20:13,030 --> 00:20:18,060
Guess what! Straight A*s in her A-Levels!

233
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:21,290
Congratulations! When'd you get your result?

234
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:22,641
Just now!

235
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:29,811
Sherali always wanted you to be a doctor...

236
00:20:32,860 --> 00:20:34,770
I know...

237
00:20:35,207 --> 00:20:38,439
I'm working on making his dream a reality.

238
00:20:38,770 --> 00:20:41,091
Tell your Granny yet?

239
00:20:42,230 --> 00:20:44,333
Sofia!
-Mum!

240
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:46,498
Sofia!

241
00:20:52,620 --> 00:20:57,960
Mum... I need to get some dresses stitched... Who's your tailor?

242
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,961
The same old...

243
00:21:00,489 --> 00:21:05,083
Why don't you go with Vishal tomorrow?

244
00:21:06,010 --> 00:21:09,375
Vishal's taking Neha shopping...

245
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:13,476
Besides, I ain't going to a mall or something...

246
00:21:18,430 --> 00:21:20,156
Excuse me...

247
00:21:26,260 --> 00:21:27,690
Congrats, Doc!

248
00:21:27,690 --> 00:21:31,960
Slow down, it's my A-Level result.

249
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:35,020
Doc's gonna need a few years...

